Dialogic Corp. is primarily engaged in the wholesale distribution of cutlery and general hardware, including handsaws; saw blades; brads, staples, and tacks; and bolts, nuts, rivets, and screws.

Founded in 1983, Dialogic Corp. is an established company that loves to hire graduates from New Jersey Institute of Technology, with 13.5% of its employees having attended New Jersey Institute of Technology. Dialogic Corp. has established itself as a great place to work in New Jersey, and it is number 14 on Zippia's list of Best Companies to Work for in Parsippany-Troy Hills, NJ.The average employee at Dialogic Corp. makes $106,764 per year. In comparison, some of its highest paying competitors, like Netgear, Tellabs, and SeaChange International, pay $134,655, $116,566, and $112,781, respectively.

Based in New Jersey, Dialogic Corp. is a medium-sized telecommunication company with 500 employees and a revenue of $132.0M.
